Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 3 (XINHUA) -- At the invitation of 
Qian Qichen, vice premier of the State Council and minister of 
foreign affairs of the People's Republic of China, Warren M. 
Christopher, secretary of state of the United States, will pay a 
visit to China from March 11 to 14, according to the spokesman 
of the Chinese Foreign Ministry here today. 
  During his visit, the U.S. secretary of state and the 
Chinese 
foreign minister will exchange views on Sino-U.S. relations and 
international issues of common concern. 

